A4.text: The Orioles won the first World Series title in 1966.

A5.text: The Orioles won World Series titles in 1966, 1970, and 1983.

A6.text: The Orioles swept the NL champion Los Angeles Dodgers in four games to register the first-ever World Series title in the franchise's 67-year history.

A7.text: With their sweep of the Dodgers, the Orioles became the last of the eight franchises that made up the American League from 1903 to 1960 to win a World Series.
